## Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js portfolio project.

### Changes Made

**1. Installed Dependencies:**
- `@vercel/analytics` (v2.0.1) - Official Vercel Analytics package
- `next-themes` (v0.4.6) - Required for the missing ThemeProvider component

**2. Files Modified:**
- `app/layout.jsx` - Updated Analytics import from `@vercel/analytics/react` to `@vercel/analytics/next` to follow the latest Next.js App Router best practices as specified in the official Vercel documentation

**3. Files Created:**
- `app/providers.jsx` - Created missing ThemeProvider wrapper component that was referenced but missing from the codebase
- `.eslintrc.json` - Added ESLint configuration for the project
- `package-lock.json` - Generated lockfile for dependency management

### Implementation Details

The Analytics component was already present in the layout but the package wasn't installed. I:
1. Fetched the latest installation instructions from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
2. Installed the `@vercel/analytics` package using npm
3. Updated the import path from `/react` to `/next` to match the framework-specific best practices for Next.js App Router
4. Fixed a missing dependency issue by installing `next-themes` and creating the providers.jsx file

The `<Analytics />` component is properly positioned at the end of the `<body>` tag in the root layout, which will track pageviews and user interactions once the site is deployed to Vercel.

### Verification

✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ Analytics component properly integrated in the root layout
✅ All dependencies installed and lockfile updated
✅ Project structure maintained and existing code preserved

### Next Steps

To enable analytics:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Navigate to your Vercel project dashboard
3. Go to Analytics in the sidebar and click "Enable"
4. Analytics will start collecting data after deployment

The implementation follows the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router projects and is production-ready.
